00:10:02.906 --> 00:10:04.726 A:middle
And that's why iPhone has

00:10:04.886 --> 00:10:06.746 A:middle
Automatic Strong Passwords,

00:10:07.406 --> 00:10:09.466 A:middle
which encourages users to use a

00:10:09.466 --> 00:10:11.806 A:middle
strong, unique password for

00:10:11.806 --> 00:10:12.816 A:middle
every single one of their

00:10:12.816 --> 00:10:15.056 A:middle
accounts, which greatly improves

00:10:15.056 --> 00:10:17.436 A:middle
their security while also being

00:10:17.436 --> 00:10:18.746 A:middle
easier to do than making the

00:10:18.746 --> 00:10:20.316 A:middle
mistake of trying to create a

00:10:20.316 --> 00:10:21.206 A:middle
password by hand.

00:10:22.466 --> 00:10:23.746 A:middle
But what if one of your users

00:10:23.856 --> 00:10:25.206 A:middle
already has a password that's

00:10:25.206 --> 00:10:25.716 A:middle
kind of weak?

00:10:26.786 --> 00:10:30.096 A:middle
Now, in Safari 13 and iOS 13,

00:10:30.796 --> 00:10:32.796 A:middle
when a user signs into a website

00:10:33.136 --> 00:10:34.536 A:middle
and Safari notices that the

00:10:34.536 --> 00:10:35.966 A:middle
password they just used was

00:10:35.966 --> 00:10:38.536 A:middle
weak, Safari will prompt the

00:10:38.536 --> 00:10:40.706 A:middle
user to go and visit the website

00:10:40.766 --> 00:10:41.806 A:middle
to change the password.

00:10:42.546 --> 00:10:43.726 A:middle
And this is at the moment of

00:10:43.726 --> 00:10:45.246 A:middle
sign-in where the user might be

00:10:45.246 --> 00:10:46.696 A:middle
thinking about what the account

00:10:46.696 --> 00:10:47.266 A:middle
means to them.

00:10:47.836 --> 00:10:50.346 A:middle
If the user accepts Safari's

00:10:50.346 --> 00:10:51.826 A:middle
offer, they'll be taken over to

00:10:51.826 --> 00:10:54.266 A:middle
Settings where they can change

00:10:54.266 --> 00:10:54.886 A:middle
their password.

00:10:55.366 --> 00:10:56.546 A:middle
And with Automatic Strong

00:10:56.546 --> 00:10:58.806 A:middle
Passwords, it's just a few taps

00:10:58.806 --> 00:11:01.846 A:middle
to get upgraded.

00:10:58.806 --> 00:11:01.846 A:middle
to get upgraded.

00:11:02.516 --> 00:11:06.596 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:11:07.096 --> 00:11:08.266 A:middle
And, of course, this feature is

00:11:08.266 --> 00:11:10.366 A:middle
on the Mac as well with Safari

00:11:10.846 --> 00:11:11.000 A:middle
13.

00:11:15.046 --> 00:11:18.066 A:middle
This flow is at its best when

00:11:18.066 --> 00:11:20.136 A:middle
your user is taken directly to

00:11:20.136 --> 00:11:22.166 A:middle
your website's Change Password

00:11:22.166 --> 00:11:24.186 A:middle
page rather than to the homepage

00:11:24.186 --> 00:11:24.596 A:middle
of the site.

00:11:25.806 --> 00:11:27.296 A:middle
And what's really cool is that

00:11:27.296 --> 00:11:28.566 A:middle
this is completely in your

00:11:28.566 --> 00:11:30.216 A:middle
control and super easy to

00:11:30.216 --> 00:11:30.656 A:middle
implement.

00:11:31.416 --> 00:11:33.826 A:middle
Websites like Twitter, GitHub,

00:11:33.826 --> 00:11:35.556 A:middle
and WordPress.com have already

00:11:35.556 --> 00:11:37.396 A:middle
adopted it.

00:11:37.396 --> 00:11:39.186 A:middle
All you have to do is put a

00:11:39.186 --> 00:11:41.056 A:middle
redirect at this path on your

00:11:41.056 --> 00:11:43.056 A:middle
server that takes the user to

00:11:43.056 --> 00:11:44.486 A:middle
your Change Password webpage,

00:11:44.966 --> 00:11:45.886 A:middle
and that's it.

00:11:46.766 --> 00:11:48.116 A:middle
The redirect can be implemented

00:11:48.246 --> 00:11:49.636 A:middle
either as a client-side redirect

00:11:50.056 --> 00:11:51.436 A:middle
or a server-side redirect.

00:11:52.096 --> 00:11:54.646 A:middle
You can learn more about the

00:11:54.646 --> 00:11:56.206 A:middle
well-known URL for changing

00:11:56.206 --> 00:11:58.586 A:middle
passwords, which is a proposed

00:11:58.586 --> 00:12:00.426 A:middle
standard at this URL.

00:11:58.586 --> 00:12:00.426 A:middle
standard at this URL.

00:12:01.736 --> 00:12:02.726 A:middle
You'll also find it pretty

00:12:02.726 --> 00:12:04.086 A:middle
easily if you search the web for

00:12:04.676 --> 00:12:04.746 A:middle
it.

00:12:08.406 --> 00:12:13.176 A:middle
And that is how iOS 13, iPadOS,

00:12:13.596 --> 00:12:16.536 A:middle
and Safari 13 help users upgrade

00:12:16.536 --> 00:12:17.426 A:middle
their weak passwords.

00:12:20.656 --> 00:12:22.236 A:middle
Some of your apps authenticate

00:12:22.236 --> 00:12:24.096 A:middle
using a third-party web service,

00:12:24.536 --> 00:12:25.936 A:middle
and if you're doing this, you're

00:12:25.936 --> 00:12:27.456 A:middle
probably using a standard like

00:12:27.456 --> 00:12:27.976 A:middle
OAuth.

00:12:29.196 --> 00:12:31.226 A:middle
The Authentication's Services

00:12:31.266 --> 00:12:31.866 A:middle
frameworks

00:12:32.246 --> 00:12:34.526 A:middle
ASWebAuthenticationSession is

00:12:34.526 --> 00:12:36.006 A:middle
the best way to do this kind of

00:12:36.006 --> 00:12:36.706 A:middle
authentication.

00:12:37.246 --> 00:12:39.976 A:middle
Once a user confirms that

00:12:39.976 --> 00:12:42.086 A:middle
they're OK with signing in, the

00:12:42.086 --> 00:12:43.916 A:middle
AuthenticationSession will use

00:12:44.306 --> 00:12:45.896 A:middle
existing signed-in accounts

00:12:45.896 --> 00:12:47.586 A:middle
through Safari's cookies and

00:12:47.586 --> 00:12:49.716 A:middle
data in order to let the user

00:12:49.716 --> 00:12:51.186 A:middle
sign-in even faster.

00:12:51.566 --> 00:12:54.836 A:middle
Sometimes the user will already

00:12:54.836 --> 00:12:56.356 A:middle
be signed in to the identity

00:12:56.356 --> 00:12:58.506 A:middle
provider, and all they have to

00:12:58.506 --> 00:13:00.566 A:middle
do is agree to signing into your

00:12:58.506 --> 00:13:00.566 A:middle
do is agree to signing into your

00:13:00.916 --> 00:13:01.006 A:middle
app.

00:13:01.736 --> 00:13:03.186 A:middle
And once they do that, they're

00:13:03.186 --> 00:13:03.666 A:middle
in.

00:13:03.756 --> 00:13:06.276 A:middle
Nice and easy.

00:13:06.456 --> 00:13:08.556 A:middle
I am so happy to be able to tell

00:13:08.556 --> 00:13:11.036 A:middle
you today that this API is now

00:13:11.036 --> 00:13:15.576 A:middle
available on macOS Catalina.

00:13:16.516 --> 00:13:19.366 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:13:19.866 --> 00:13:23.616 A:middle
On macOS Catalina, this API uses

00:13:23.616 --> 00:13:25.446 A:middle
the user's preferred web browser

00:13:25.686 --> 00:13:27.386 A:middle
for signing in if that web

00:13:27.386 --> 00:13:28.326 A:middle
browser supports it.

00:13:28.376 --> 00:13:30.186 A:middle
And this is really great,

00:13:30.606 --> 00:13:31.936 A:middle
because it means that all of

00:13:31.936 --> 00:13:33.806 A:middle
your users will have their

00:13:33.806 --> 00:13:35.696 A:middle
browser's password manager or

00:13:35.696 --> 00:13:37.036 A:middle
