00:13:37.036 --> 00:13:38.476 A:middle
available to them in order to

00:13:38.476 --> 00:13:40.266 A:middle
help get them signed in.

00:13:42.416 --> 00:13:43.816 A:middle
If you're using the

00:13:43.816 --> 00:13:46.156 A:middle
AuthenticationSession API, it

00:13:46.156 --> 00:13:47.456 A:middle
has a few new features for you

00:13:47.456 --> 00:13:48.216 A:middle
to use this year.

00:13:48.326 --> 00:13:51.546 A:middle
And the first is a more private

00:13:51.546 --> 00:13:53.136 A:middle
kind of sign-in.

00:13:54.576 --> 00:13:55.296 A:middle
Because the

00:13:55.296 --> 00:13:57.216 A:middle
AuthenticationSession shares

00:13:57.216 --> 00:13:58.726 A:middle
website data with Safari,

00:13:59.686 --> 00:14:01.586 A:middle
ASWebAuthenticationSession

00:13:59.686 --> 00:14:01.586 A:middle
ASWebAuthenticationSession

00:14:01.676 --> 00:14:03.686 A:middle
enables a single sign-on

00:14:03.686 --> 00:14:04.366 A:middle
experience.

00:14:05.496 --> 00:14:08.116 A:middle
New to iOS 13, your app can

00:14:08.116 --> 00:14:10.436 A:middle
choose to deliver a more private

00:14:10.436 --> 00:14:12.716 A:middle
experience, an experience that

00:14:12.716 --> 00:14:14.896 A:middle
won't leave users logged into

00:14:14.896 --> 00:14:16.446 A:middle
the identity provider in their

00:14:16.446 --> 00:14:18.306 A:middle
web browser after they've signed

00:14:18.306 --> 00:14:19.466 A:middle
into your app.

00:14:20.456 --> 00:14:22.036 A:middle
If your app asks for this

00:14:22.036 --> 00:14:24.546 A:middle
experience, users won't see this

00:14:24.546 --> 00:14:25.026 A:middle
