00:14:25.886 --> 00:14:27.726 A:middle
Instead, they'll be taken

00:14:27.726 --> 00:14:28.966 A:middle
directly to the identity

00:14:28.966 --> 00:14:30.826 A:middle
provider in order to get signed

00:14:31.416 --> 00:14:31.496 A:middle
in.

00:14:33.576 --> 00:14:35.266 A:middle
To do this, set the

00:14:35.266 --> 00:14:36.616 A:middle
prefersEphemeral

00:14:36.616 --> 00:14:38.836 A:middle
WebBrowserSession property on

00:14:38.836 --> 00:14:40.626 A:middle
the session to true before

00:14:40.626 --> 00:14:41.426 A:middle
starting the session.

00:14:42.696 --> 00:14:44.376 A:middle
By doing this, you give your

00:14:44.436 --> 00:14:47.396 A:middle
users more privacy and avoid

00:14:47.396 --> 00:14:49.486 A:middle
that confirmation dialog, which

00:14:49.486 --> 00:14:50.796 A:middle
overall might be a better

00:14:50.796 --> 00:14:52.426 A:middle
experience for your app.

00:14:54.296 --> 00:14:56.806 A:middle
Next, supporting multiple

00:14:56.806 --> 00:14:57.266 A:middle
windows.

00:14:58.706 --> 00:15:00.126 A:middle
In iOS 12, the

00:14:58.706 --> 00:15:00.126 A:middle
In iOS 12, the

00:15:00.126 --> 00:15:02.586 A:middle
AuthenticationSession API didn't

00:15:02.586 --> 00:15:05.146 A:middle
need any information about view

00:15:05.146 --> 00:15:07.186 A:middle
or windows from you in order to

00:15:07.186 --> 00:15:08.236 A:middle
display its interface.

00:15:09.236 --> 00:15:11.326 A:middle
This is because the API was iOS

00:15:11.326 --> 00:15:14.186 A:middle
only, and almost all apps drew

