security keys in Safari through

00:16:26.906 --> 00:16:28.336 A:middle
the WebAuthentication standard.

00:16:29.156 --> 00:16:31.246 A:middle
I am really happy about this

00:16:31.246 --> 00:16:33.056 A:middle
support, especially because I

00:16:33.056 --> 00:16:34.096 A:middle
know that a number of you have

00:16:34.096 --> 00:16:35.586 A:middle
been asking for it.

00:16:36.736 --> 00:16:39.266 A:middle
Depending on who or what you're

00:16:39.266 --> 00:16:41.126 A:middle
protecting and the threat models

00:16:41.126 --> 00:16:42.986 A:middle
that you're concerned about, you

00:16:42.986 --> 00:16:45.066 A:middle
might consider tying user

00:16:45.066 --> 00:16:47.126 A:middle
authentication to the physical

00:16:47.126 --> 00:16:48.046 A:middle
presence of some kind of

00:16:48.046 --> 00:16:49.566 A:middle
hardware device.

00:16:50.696 --> 00:16:54.346 A:middle
Safari 13 supports USB-based

00:16:54.796 --> 00:16:57.246 A:middle
FIDO2-compliant devices with the

00:16:57.246 --> 00:16:58.436 A:middle
WebAuthentication standard.

00:16:59.566 --> 00:17:01.656 A:middle
It's available as an

00:16:59.566 --> 00:17:01.656 A:middle
It's available as an

00:17:02.426 --> 00:17:05.185 A:middle
experimental feature in Seed 1

00:17:05.185 --> 00:17:07.626 A:middle
of macOS Catalina, and it'll be

00:17:07.626 --> 00:17:09.236 A:middle
on by default in Seed 2.

00:17:10.175 --> 00:17:11.786 A:middle
You can also try it out right

00:17:11.786 --> 00:17:13.465 A:middle
now if you download Safari

00:17:13.465 --> 00:17:14.356 A:middle
Technology Preview.

00:17:14.955 --> 00:17:17.816 A:middle
If you're interested in

00:17:17.816 --> 00:17:19.976 A:middle
supporting USB security keys,

00:17:20.506 --> 00:17:22.445 A:middle
it's really important to offer a

00:17:22.445 --> 00:17:24.236 A:middle
great account recovery story,

00:17:25.435 --> 00:17:26.935 A:middle
just in case your user's key

00:17:27.205 --> 00:17:29.816 A:middle
gets lost, stolen, or broken.

00:17:31.276 --> 00:17:33.196 A:middle
And designing account recovery

00:17:33.336 --> 00:17:35.316 A:middle
systems when a hardware token is

00:17:35.316 --> 00:17:37.996 A:middle
involved is really important,

00:17:37.996 --> 00:17:38.706 A:middle
but it's not always

00:17:38.706 --> 00:17:39.336 A:middle
straightforward.

00:17:40.486 --> 00:17:42.286 A:middle
So unless you are already in

00:17:42.286 --> 00:17:44.246 A:middle
this business or were seriously

00:17:44.246 --> 00:17:46.106 A:middle
considering getting into it,

00:17:46.856 --> 00:17:48.546 A:middle
it's more likely that one or

00:17:48.546 --> 00:17:50.076 A:middle
more of the other areas that I

00:17:50.076 --> 00:17:51.816 A:middle
cover today will be more

00:17:51.816 --> 00:17:53.956 A:middle
relevant for your users, your

00:17:53.956 --> 00:17:54.976 A:middle
apps, and your websites.

00:18:00.266 --> 00:18:01.866 A:middle
If you develop an app with user

00:18:01.866 --> 00:18:04.386 A:middle
accounts, I have three takeaways

00:18:04.426 --> 00:18:05.286 A:middle
from what we've talked about

00:18:05.286 --> 00:18:05.506 A:middle
today.

00:18:06.936 --> 00:18:09.326 A:middle
First, strongly consider

00:18:09.326 --> 00:18:11.036 A:middle
adopting Sign In with Apple.

00:18:12.196 --> 00:18:13.946 A:middle
For your users, the best

00:18:13.946 --> 00:18:15.736 A:middle
password is no password,

00:18:16.306 --> 00:18:17.896 A:middle
especially when it's backed by

00:18:17.896 --> 00:18:19.666 A:middle
two-factor authentication and

00:18:19.666 --> 00:18:21.000 A:middle
great biometrics.

00:18:22.236 --> 00:18:25.126 A:middle
Two, make signing into your app

00:18:25.476 --> 00:18:28.086 A:middle
a one-tap experience using the

00:18:28.086 --> 00:18:29.676 A:middle
Authentication Services

00:18:29.766 --> 00:18:30.286 A:middle
framework.

00:18:31.056 --> 00:18:32.406 A:middle
Users don't even need to see a

00:18:32.406 --> 00:18:34.266 A:middle
keyboard anymore to get signed

00:18:34.706 --> 00:18:34.796 A:middle
in.

00:18:35.476 --> 00:18:37.446 A:middle
And finally, implement the

00:18:37.446 --> 00:18:39.036 A:middle
well-known URL for changing

00:18:39.036 --> 00:18:39.686 A:middle
passwords.

00:18:40.456 --> 00:18:42.076 A:middle
It's really easy to do, takes

00:18:42.076 --> 00:18:44.056 A:middle
just a moment, and it makes a

00:18:44.056 --> 00:18:46.146 A:middle
huge difference when Safari is

00:18:46.146 --> 00:18:47.586 A:middle
going to try to help your users

00:18:47.756 --> 00:18:48.906 A:middle
upgrade their passwords.

